<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1437,251,1538]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,251,277]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Recognized by the following set of features: dorsum dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1044,1128,251,278]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
); antennal segment II with relatively broad, apical, white annulation that is as wide as half of interocular distance (
<figureCitation box="[1144,1227,287,314]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
); posterior lobe of pronotum with distinct swelling medially (
<figureCitation box="[622,703,323,350]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
); scutellum distinctly convex, with longitudinal swelling medially (
<figureCitation box="[160,241,359,386]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
); anal vein with short, yellow stripe subapically (
<figureCitation box="[788,869,359,386]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
); endosoma membranous; distal sclerotized part of ductus seminis (dss) short, rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[597,726,395,422]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs 14a, b</figureCitation>
); ventro-apical margin of ductus seminis inside endosoma with deep incision (
<figureCitation box="[315,413,431,458]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 14b</figureCitation>
); left paramere apical process with short basolateral outgrowth (
<figureCitation box="[1132,1260,431,458]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs 14c, d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
