<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,467,493]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Redescription</emphasis>
. Female. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[477,669,467,493]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">COLORATION</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[685,767,467,494]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
). Dorsum dark brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1027,1089,467,494]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown with dark yellow areas medially and laterally; antenna dark brown; antennal segment II with relatively broad, apical, white annulation that is as wide as half of interocular distance; labium dark brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[951,1037,539,566]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Thorax</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Pronotum, mesoscutum, scutellum and hemelytron</emphasis>
. Dark brown; anal vein with short, yellow stripe subapically. 
<emphasis box="[1025,1207,575,601]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Thoracic pleura</emphasis>
. Dark brown; metathoracic scent gland evaporative areas tinged with dark yellow posteriorly. 
<emphasis box="[993,1046,612,637]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Legs</emphasis>
. Pro– and mesocoxae dark brown; metacoxa yellow, dark brown basally; femora dark castaneous, with yellow annulation subapically; metafemur with broad, yellow annulation basally; tibiae dark castaneous; tarsi brown, tinged with dark yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1238,1348,683,710]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Black, tinged with dark yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[432,803,719,746]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">TEXTURE AND VESTITURE</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[819,901,719,746]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[922,1008,719,746]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Thorax</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Mesoscutum, scutellum, and hemelytron</emphasis>
. Covered with short, fine, dense, recumbent setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[767,940,755,781]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">STRUCTURE</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[955,1036,755,782]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1056,1142,755,782]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Thorax</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1156,1267,756,781]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Pronotum</emphasis>
. Posterior lobe with distinct swelling medially. 
<emphasis box="[504,614,791,817]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Scutellum</emphasis>
. With strongly convex, broad longitudinal swelling medially. 
<emphasis box="[1298,1429,791,817]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Hemelytron</emphasis>
. Surface between R+M vein and medial fracture rugose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,904,827,854]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Abdomen</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[920,1026,827,853]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Endosoma membranous (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs 14a, b</figureCitation>
); distal sclerotized part of ductus seminis (dss) short, rectangular, with transparent portion dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1422,863,890]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs 14a, b</figureCitation>
); ventro-apical margin of ductus seminis inside endosoma with deep incision (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1100,899,926]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 14b</figureCitation>
); left paramere C-shaped, apical process with short process basolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[650,779,935,962]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs 14c, d</figureCitation>
); right paramere sickle-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1138,1239,935,962]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs 14e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1437,251,1538]" box="[199,867,971,998]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Male. Like female in color, structure, texture, and vestiture.</paragraph>
