<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1437,251,1538]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1260,1286]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Remarks</emphasis>
. Most like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1909" box="[438,583,1259,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Peltidocylapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis box="[438,583,1259,1285]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">P. scutellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in sharing the clavus having a short, yellow stripe apically (
<figureCitation box="[1265,1380,1259,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs 6a, b</figureCitation>
), the distal portion of ductus seminis inside endosoma (dss) short, not caliciform with ventro-apical margin concave in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[284,460,1331,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs 14a, b, f, h</figureCitation>
), and the left paramere apical process lateral outgrowth short (
<figureCitation box="[1153,1321,1331,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs 14c, d, i, j</figureCitation>
). It can be distinguished by the presence of deeper incision on ventro-apical margin of the dss (
<figureCitation box="[1094,1192,1367,1394]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 14b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
